snippet.textDisplay: OMG!!! People that classify this performance as tacky, no class, etc need to get out a bit more to other countries, educate their minds a bit more. Learn about different cultures and different types of performing art, specifically Shakira's performance.  Her Arabic dance is very beautiful, it shows her heritage (dad is from Lebanon) why is that tacky? The tongue "thingy" like some people call the gesture, is not offensive, is not tacky, is a cultural gesture! One is a gesture from her Arab heritage, second is a gesture we do in carnivals in Colombia, specifically the Barranquilla carnival. She is from Barranquilla Colombia. When she moves her hips really rapidly in one part of her performance, she is dancing Mapale, a traditional dance in Colombian culture, from the pacific coast of Colombia. Then she dances Champeta a traditional Colombian dance with roots in our African heritage. Shakira's performance was full of grace, full of fun, and honouring her roots (Latin and Arab)
